lack neighborhoods vulnerable to conflict, where black lives are seemingly expendable, and where black citizens are held responsible for their own oppression. You Can't Stop the Revolution serves as a reminder that community empowerment is still possible in neighborhoods experiencing police brutality and interpersonal violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAfrican AmericansxViolence againstzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aPolice brutalityzUnited Statesy21st century. 0aPolice-community relationszUnited Statesy21st century. 0aProtest movementszUnited Statesy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aactivists.  aafrican american studies.  aafrican americans.  ablack citizens.  ablack community.  ablack lives matter.  ablack lives.  ablack neighborhoods.  ablack.  acommunity empowerment.  acrime prevention.  acriminal justice.  acriminology.  adeath.  adiscrimination.  aempowerment.  aethnic studies.  aferguson.  amass incarceration.  aneighborhood crime.  anonfiction.  apolice brutality.  apolice conflict.  apolitical engagement.  apolitical movements.  apolitics.  aprejudice.  aprotests.  arace.  aracism.  aresistance.  asocial issues.  aviolence in society.  aviolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook packa